      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LAST HARD COPY (9) missed the start and then raced up to four wide before finding the lead last start so it was no surprise to see him fade late. Draws wide so may need luck but was going very well prior including a win from the back row at this circuit and distance two back and a couple of Group placings prior. ULTIMATE MIKI (5) has won his two starts at this circuit and distance since crossing from the east for this campaign. Race wide from the back row but proved too strong last week. Building an impressive strike rate and could deliver again. WHEN IN VEGAS (3) raced three wide without cover and worked but toughed out a win when resuming as a hot favourite. Draws better and should strip fitter. WICKED HUSTLER (10) had to work from this row here last week but dug deep to win. Must respect.",
